lektiven Rezeption des Navalisten Mahan das ursprünglich militärisch begründete Kalkül der deutschen Flottenrüstung zu dem in sich widersprüchlichen Abschreckungskonzept der Risikoflotte wandelte.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aNaval strategyxHistoryy19th century. 0aNaval strategyxHistoryy20th century. 0aSea-powerzGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 0aSea-powerzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 4aImperialismus. 4aMarine. 4aMilitärgeschichte. 4aTirpitzplan. 4aVorgeschichte Erster Weltkrieg. 70(DE-588)4054160-50(DE-627)1061637010(DE-576)209107677aSeemacht2gnd 70(DE-588)4057952-90(DE-627)1061490750(DE-576)209124202aStrategie2gnd 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aBesteck, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI0 cprintz978348656671040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978348659620540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783486596205423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783486596205/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014